Set Up Salesforce Permissions for the Event Monitoring Analytics App

To use the Event Monitoring Analytics App, enable CRM Analytics, assign permission set licenses, and create/assign permission sets. 

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS:

* Access Event Monitoring Analytics Templates and Apps
* Manage CRM Analytics Templated Apps
* Edit CRM Analytics Dataflows

Note: The Event Monitoring Analytics App is only for data provided as part of your subscription. Do not use it to upload or access other data.

Each license provides access to up to 10 users and has a 50 million row data storage limit. Additional rows can be purchased for $100 million.

The sample data remains in the app until overwritten, with event log file data available for the past 30 days (24 hours on Developer Edition orgs).

You can use the Event Monitoring Analytics App with or without CRM Analytics platform access.

Event Monitoring Analytics App User Permissions:

* Use CRM Analytics Templated Apps
* Access Event Monitoring Analytics Templates and Apps
* Manage CRM Analytics Templated Apps
* Edit CRM Analytics Dataflows

Follow these steps for best results when setting up the Event Monitoring Analytics app:

1. Identify Event Monitoring Analytics App User Types
2. Enable CRM Analytics and Event Monitoring Integration with CRM Analytics
3. Select User Permissions and Assign Users to Event Monitoring Analytics App Permission Sets
4. Create and Share the Event Monitoring Analytics App
title: Setting Up Salesforce Permissions for Event Monitoring Analytics App
